Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light grey-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Teisagoras. Pencilled '70'. Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.122, 15. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0214.25.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1077)
